  "caption": "Figure 4. Hepadnaviridae . Phylogenetic tree based on the polymerase genes of 50 selected members of the family Hepadnaviridae . Maximum likelihood trees were produced using the General Time Reversible model with a gamma distribution of variation including invariant sites, and conducted using MEGA7 ( Kumar et al., 2016 ). Numbers indicate where bootstrap support for branches was > 70%. Circles at tips are coloured according to species; unclassified viruses have unfilled circles. This phylogenetic tree and corresponding sequence alignment are available to download from the Resources page .",
